<p />
V. Sliva, T. Murata, and S. M. Shatz, &ldquo;Protocol Specification Design Using an Object-Based Petri Net Formalism,&rdquo; <em>Int. Journal of Software Engineering and Knowledge Engineering</em>, Feb. 1999, Vol. 9, No. 1, pp. 97-125.
<h4><a name="1998"></a> <font color="#8b0000">1998</font> </h4>
 A. Khetarpal, S. M. Shatz, and S. Tu, &ldquo;Applying an Object-Based Petri Net to the Modeling of Communication Primitives for Distributed Software,&rdquo; <em>Proceedings of the High Performance Computing Conference (HPC98)</em>, Boston, Mass., April 1998, pp. 404-409.
<p />
C. Black, S. M. Shatz, and S. Tu, &ldquo;A Query Language for Automated General Analysis of Concurrent Ada Programs,&rdquo; <em>International Journal of Computer Systems Science and Engineering</em>, Vol. 13, No. 2, March 1998, pp. 83-95. <br /><a href="http://www.cs.uic.edu/~shatz/papers/tql.pdf" target="_top">PDF File </a>
<p />
A. Newman, S. M. Shatz, and X. Xie, &ldquo;An Approach to Object System Modeling by State-Based Object Petri Nets,&rdquo; <em>Int. Journal of Circuits, Systems, and Computers</em>, Feb. 1998, Vol. 8, No. 1, pp. 1-20. <br /><a href="http://www.cs.uic.edu/~shatz/papers/sbopn.pdf" target="_top">PDF File </a>
<h4><a name="1997"></a> <font color="#8b0000">1997</font> </h4>
 M. Altaher, U. Buy, S. Shatz, C. Yu, D. Hier, and W. Panko, &ldquo;A Computer-Based System for Problem List Maintenance and Medical Informatics,&rdquo; <em>19th Annual IEEE International Conference on Engineering in Medicine and Biology</em>, Chicago, Oct. 1997, pp. 949-952.
<p />
C. Sashidhar and S. M. Shatz, &ldquo;Design and Implementation Issues for Supporting Callback Prodedures in RPC-Based Distributed Software,&rdquo; <em>21st Annual International Computer Software and Applications Conference (COMPSAC-97)</em>, Washington, D.C., Aug. 1997, pp. 460-466.
<p />
R. Gedela and S. M. Shatz, &ldquo;Formal Modeling of Advanced Tasking in Ada: A Petri Net Perspective,&rdquo; <em>2nd International Workshop on Software Engineering for Parallel and Distributed Systems (PDSE-97)</em>, Boston, May, 1997, pp. 4-14.
<h4><a name="1996"></a> <font color="#8b0000">1996</font> </h4>
 S. M. Shatz, S. Tu, T. Murata, and S. Duri, &ldquo;An Application of Petri Net Reduction for Ada Tasking Deadlock Analysis,&rdquo; <em>IEEE Trans. on Parallel and Distributed Systems</em>, Vol. 7, No. 12, Dec. 1996, pp. 1307-1322. <br /><a href="http://www.cs.uic.edu/~shatz/papers/redu.with.figs.ps" target="_top">Postscript File</a>
<p />
C. Sashidhar and S. M. Shatz, &ldquo;Shared Program Variables for Distributed Sequential Programs,&rdquo; <em>Proc. of the 11th Int. Conf. on Systems Engineering</em>, Las Vegas, Nevada, July 1996, pp. 584-589.
<p />
T. Murata, T. Sazuki, and S. M. Shatz, &ldquo;Fuzzy-Timing High-Level Petri Net Model of a Real-Time Network Protocol,&rdquo; <em>Proc. of the 1996 Int. Technical Conf. on Circuits/Systems, Computers and Communications</em>, Seoul, Korea, July 1996, pp. 1170-1173.
<p />
V. Sliva, T. Murata, and S. M. Shatz, &ldquo;A Method for Applying G-Nets to Communication Protocols,&rdquo; <em>Proc. of the 8th Int. Conf. on Software Engineering and Knowledge Engineering, (SEKE-96)</em>, Lake Tahoe, Nevada, June 1996, pp. 145-152.
<h4><a name="1995"></a> <font color="#8b0000">1995</font> </h4>
 L. Lilien, S. M. Shatz, and S. Damerla, &ldquo;Redistribution of Hierarchically Structured Software in Response to Distributed System Site Crashes,&rdquo; <em>International Journal of Computer Systems Science and Engineering</em>, Vol. 10, No. 3, July 1995, pp. 144-155. 
<h4><a name="1994"></a> <font color="#8b0000">1994</font> </h4>
 S. Duri, U. Buy, R. Devarapalli, and S. M. Shatz, &ldquo;Application and Experimental Evaluation of State Space Reduction Methods for Deadlock Analysis in Ada,&rdquo; <em>ACM Transactions on Software Engineering Methodology</em>, Vol. 3, No. 4, Oct. 1994, pp. 340-380. 
<h4><a name="1993"></a> <font color="#8b0000">1993</font> </h4>
 S. Duri, U. Buy, R. Devarapalli and S.M. Shatz, &ldquo;Using State Space Methods for Deadlock Analysis in Ada Tasking,&rdquo; <em>Proceedings of the International Symposium on Software Testing and Analysis (ISSTA-93), </em>pp. 51-60, May, 1993.
<p />
S.M. Shatz, <em>Development of Distributed Software: Concepts and Tools</em>, New York: Macmillan Publishing Company,1993.
<h4><a name="1992"></a> <font color="#8b0000">1992</font> </h4>
 S.M. Shatz, J.P. Wang and M. Goto, &ldquo;Task Allocation for Maximizing Reliability of Distributed Computer Systems,&rdquo; <em>IEEE Transactions on Computers, </em>Vol. 41, No. 9, pp. 1156-1168, September, 1992.
<p />
S. Damerla and S.M. Shatz, &ldquo;Software Complexity and Ada Rendevous: Metrics Based on Nondeterminism,&rdquo; <em>Journal of Systems and Software,</em> Vol. 17, pp. 119-127, March, 1992.
<h4><a name="1991"></a> <font color="#8b0000">1991</font> </h4>
 T. Murata, R. Bhatia and S. Shatz, &ldquo;Markov Chain Reduction and Analysis of GSPN Models for Task Allocation in Distributed Systems,&rdquo; <em>International Journal on Microelectronics and Reliability,</em> (Special Issue on Petri Nets), Vol. 31, No. 4, pp. 727-746, 1991.
<p />
S. Damerla and S.M. Shatz, &ldquo;A Software Complexity Perspective on Nondeterminism Used to Support Intertask Communications,&rdquo; <em>Proceedings of the International Phoenix Conference on Computers and Communications, </em>Scottsdale, Arizona, pp. 280-286, March, 1991. </div><!-- /patternTopic-->
